Reasoning: The paper discusses the limitations of current machine vision systems and proposes the concept of universal representations for vision, which can be applied to a wide range of vision problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large labelled datasets and high-capacity models, which are common in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The concept of universal representations also involves learning a universal feature space, which is related to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the recognition of text and cat breeds, which are related to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, respectively.
